 executive of unifirst who spent his entire professional life supplying uniforms and apparel to some of the biggest manufacturing companies died on tuesday in boston he was the cause was complications of pneumonia a company representative saidat unifirst mr croatti led what began in 3 as a familyowned business run by his father aldo from a converted horse barn in boston where one washing machine cleaned uniforms for factory workers he turned it into the secondlargest supplier and cleaner of uniforms and garments in the united states with about  billion in annual revenuewhen he took over as chief executive in  succeeding his father unifirst based in wilmington mass had about  million in revenuetoday unifirst supplies uniforms to nearly two million people working for  businesses in the united states canada and europe many in the food service health care and energy industries archer daniels midland berkshire hathaway cocacola costco and goodyear are among its customers continue reading the main story advertisement continue reading the main story it also specializes in decontaminating garments worn by workers at nuclear facilitiesmr croatti gave the company a promotional boost in  when he put on a green unifirst uniform a mustache and a shoulderlength gray wig for an episode of the cbs reality series “undercover boss” pretending to be a new employee named mike daniels he visited several of unifirst’s  facilities where workers taught him how to load dirty uniforms into giant washing machines and package clothes for delivery undercover boss  preview unifirst video by cbs the original broadcast was viewed by more than 3 million people and the company has credited mr croatti’s appearance with attracting new business“ron took a huge risk by doing this as we had no editing rights” said adam soreff unifirst’s director of marketing “it ended up being great advertising and huge exposure”in the episode mr croatti revealed some of his personal life including his grandfather’s death in an accident involving an industrial clothes washer the program also showed him relaxing at his home in londonderry nh playing with his model train collectionunifirst which went public in 83 under the name interstate uniform service company has remained in the hands of the croatti family which controls a majority of the voting shares mr croatti’s sister cynthia is a board member and executive vice president two of his sons michael and matthew work for the company which changed its name to unifirst in 8 newsletter sign up continue reading the main story please verify youre not a robot by clicking the box invalid email address please reenter you must select a newsletter to subscribe to sign up you agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for the new york timess products and services thank you for subscribing an error has occurred please try again later you are already subscribed to this email view all new york times newsletters see sample manage email preferences not you privacy policy opt out or contact us anytime last year for the first time mr croatti joined the list of the  bestpaid chief executives in the united states according to an annual ranking done by equilar for the new york times he made the list because of a large stock award that pushed the value of his  pay package to  million advertisement continue reading the main story ronald daniel croatti was born on april  3 in boston his mother was the former alba olney his paternal grandparents had emigrated from rimini italy in mr croatti was  when he began working on and off at unifirst at that time the company was called national overall dry cleaning company he was hired officially in  not long after he graduated from san diego state universitybesides his sons michael and matthew and his sister he is survived by his wife carol another son aldo a daughter melissa and nine grandchildrenin the “undercover boss” episode mr croatti mentioned that he was grooming his son michael a senior vice pre